Ad Text:
The Transformation Specialist plays a critical role in supporting the delivery of complex change initiatives at Team Super, particularly across areas of remediation, data integrity and other merger related initiatives.

This role blends deep analytical capability with technical skills and project leadership to ensure the Fund delivers accurate member-focussed outcomes, with the Transformation Specialist responsible for interrogating problem spaces, documenting findings and deliver project outcomes in line with regulatory requirements, member expectations, and our organisational strategy.

Key Responsibilities

Leading the analysis, preparation and production of business requirements, change impact assessments and gap assessments, as directed by the Executive Manager, Programme;

Working with the Executive Manager, Programme to develop business cases, and own and develop key project artefacts including business requirements, change impact assessments and other specifications across the business;

Partnering with internal risk, technology and data, and operations teams and external providers including the Administrator to ensure data lineage, quality, integrity and risks are understood and embedded into solution designs;

Collaborating with broader business and project stakeholders to document regulatory, operational or systems issues into actionable insights, business requirements, and project plans, and ensure initiatives can be managed and delivered in an effective, auditable, and member-focussed manner;

Providing subject matter leadership across initiatives as required, and champion Team Super’s Project Management Framework and practices;

Facilitating and supporting discovery workshops and other stakeholder engagements to advance projects and discovery;

Proactively identifying and escalating issues and risks associated with projects and initiatives;

Developing and maintaining project and initiative work backlogs, and assisting the Executive Manager Programme and broader leadership team in prioritising backlog items;

Any other duties as requested by your line manager.

Qualifications

Demonstrated experience – at least 5 years of Business Analyst, Systems Analyst or Technical Analyst experience in superannuation, financial services or related regulated activities (mandatory)

Bachelor’s degree in business, science, science engineering, IT or economics (desired)

RG146 accreditation (or willing to undertake) (desired)

Skills & Experience

Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with experience contributing to discussions at senior level

Strong knowledge of superannuation operations and regulatory obligations preferred, with industry qualifications (RG146 or equivalent) highly regarded

Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with proficiency in various project management disciplines desirable

Excellent skills in stakeholder management and facilitating discussions across various levels of seniority

Collaborative and pragmatic mindset, with the ability to build and maintain strong working relationships with colleagues, clients, and key stakeholders;

Ability to balance detail-oriented analysis with delivery-focussed project oversight

Ability to maintain confidentiality and discretion;

Ability to work within a self-directed culture and navigate ambiguity;

Possess intermediate to advanced level skills, knowledge and experience in the practical application of Microsoft Office applications including but not limited to Word, Excel, PowerPoint, SharePoint and Outlook.

If this sounds like you, please click the Apply button. We look forward to hearing from you.
